# Faster R-CNN — Tahrir Traffic Detection

## Folder Structure

```
FasterRCNN/
├── dataloader.py          ← your existing dataloader
├── setup_verify.py        ← Part 1: install check + 5-sample test
├── train.py               ← Part 2: training (60 epochs, MLflow)
├── evaluate.py            ← Part 3: metrics, detection images, MLflow
├── requirements.txt
└── outputs/
    ├── best_faster_rcnn.pth
    ├── last_faster_rcnn.pth
    ├── eval_results.json
    └── detection_images/
```

---

## Step-by-Step: GPU Setup & Running

### 1. Check your CUDA version
```bash
nvidia-smi
```
Note the CUDA version shown (e.g. 12.1, 11.8).

### 2. Install PyTorch with CUDA support

**For CUDA 12.1:**
```bash
pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121
```
**For CUDA 11.8:**
```bash
pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu118
```

### 3. Install remaining dependencies
```bash
cd FasterRCNN
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Part 1 — Verify setup
```bash
python setup_verify.py
```
You should see:
- All libraries listed with versions
- `CUDA available: True` and your GPU name
- 5 sample images loaded with box counts

### 5. Part 2 — Train (60 epochs)
```bash
python train.py
```
- Automatically uses GPU if available
- Saves `outputs/best_faster_rcnn.pth` whenever val loss improves
- Open MLflow UI in another terminal to watch live:
```bash
mlflow ui
# then open http://localhost:5000 in your browser
```

### 6. Part 3 — Evaluate
```bash
python evaluate.py
```
Outputs:
- `outputs/eval_results.json` — all metrics
- `outputs/detection_images/` — 10 sample images with bounding boxes
- MLflow run with all metrics logged

---

## Tips for Best GPU Performance

| Tip | What to Change |
|-----|----------------|
| Increase batch size | Set `BATCH_SIZE = 4` in `train.py` if your VRAM allows |
| Faster data loading | Increase `num_workers=4` in DataLoader calls |
| Mixed precision | Wrap training loop with `torch.cuda.amp.autocast()` for ~2x speed |
| Monitor GPU usage | Run `watch -n 1 nvidia-smi` in a separate terminal |

---

## MLflow Tracked Metrics

**Training:** `train_loss`, `val_loss`, `lr` (per epoch)

**Evaluation:** `mAP_50`, `mAP_50_95`, `precision`, `recall`, `avg_inference_ms`, `fps`, `AP_<class>` per class
